items.name: That '70s Wiki
items.title: That '70s Wiki
items.headline: Hang Out With That 70's Show!
items.desc:
Hi there and welcome to the world of That 70's Show - don't worry, It's a Wonderful Life.
At That 70's Show, you have a bunch of crazy and awesome teenagers week after week putting themselves out there in the wide world of Point Place, an excellent crew that strives to make this show as accurate, funny and charming as an excellent show should be and one of the most brilliant Sitcom directors in the buisness - David Trainer.

Set in 1976 and spanning 4 years (show time) and 8 years (real time), we watch Eric Forman (Topher Grace), a socially awkward teen with an obsession with Star Wars and a beautiful neighbour by the name of Donna Pinciotti (Laura Prepon). While 'getting the girl' Eric has to deal with his well intentioned but overbearing parents, Red Forman (Kurtwood Smith) and Kitty Forman (Debra Jo Rupp). As he faces the next four years of his life stuck in the final years of high school, he has best friend and 'rebel' Steven Hyde (Danny Masterson) to convince him to do stupid stuff, although, a lot of stupid stuff has already been done by Michael Kelso (Ashton Kutcher). 

Kelso brings with him his annoying and shallow girlfriend, Jackie Burkhart (Mila Kunis) - head cheerleader, queen bee and rather dispises Eric and Hyde (at first, that is). The final chocolate chip to this cookie of crazy is Fez (Wilmer Valderrama), loveable, candy-crazy, girl-chasing Fez.

The six of them spend their time in Eric's basement, watching TV, eating popsicles and generally being as laid back as a teen in the 70's can - but don't think that doesn't make it exciting! They take the journey through teen years into adult-hood from getting your first car to getting married!

The road is bumpy and long, but they made it in the end...

This show has brought families together, made them laugh and cry along with the characters they have grown to love, and we have all watched them grow up - the awkward way. On TV. Join with me, laugh with me. Laugh with them. 

That 70's Show.

items.name: Peep Show Wiki
items.title: Peep Show Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Peep Show wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to Peep Show Wiki, the wiki about the television series Peep Show that anyone can edit.

Peep Show follows the lives of two men from their twenties to thirties, Mark Corrigan (Mitchell), who has steady employment for most of the series, and Jeremy "Jez" Usbourne (Webb), an unemployed would-be musician. The pair met at the fictional Dartmouth University, and now share a flat in Croydon, South London. Mark is initially a loan manager at the fictional JLB Credit, later becoming a waiter, and then a bathroom supplies salesman. He is financially secure, but awkward and socially inept, with a pessimistic and cynical attitude. Jeremy, having split up with his girlfriend Big Suze prior to the first episode, now lives in Mark's spare room. He usually has a much more optimistic and energetic outlook on the world than Mark, yet his self-proclaimed talent as a musician has yet to be recognised, and he is not as popular or attractive as he would like to think himself, although he is more successful with the opposite sex than Mark.
